title: Himalayan Art (Art History Ebook).pdf
description:
Himalayan art - wall-painting and sculpture in Ladakh, Lahaul, and Spiti, the Siwalik Ranges, Nepal, Sikkim, and Bhutan.

1968 | NY Graphic Society | Eng | 295 p | 50.5 MB

The unique and Fascinating artistic heritage of the Himalayan regions is still virtually unknown to tin' general reader. The northern mountain regions of the Indian subcontinent abound in treasures of religious and mythological art astounding beauty. The wall paintings and sculptures of the temples and monasteries, many of them thousands of years old, represent a commentary on the changing forms and influences in Indian art
